<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_e82a0c9b-ae2d-4f87-92c5-0bc3368b3ab4" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/></meta><sptc>H3V3</sptc><title id="_a3f6c146-6ef6-4e96-be1f-062a0120b721">Avoidance of spread of fire between buildings on adjoining allotments</title><archive-num>2019: V2.3.1.3</archive-num><subclause id="_20964c9d-c78c-49c6-8cb2-d68e761072cc" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_94a55a96-ca69-41e2-b9ae-217234ade6e4">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Compliance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1869_0.14.0.xml#_9d47c3bf-6a3c-4c83-ad7a-1a018d707131" id="_e0e0b41a-cafe-4f2d-9fe7-06f6dad6ab8e" scope="local" type="subclause">H3P1(2)</xref> to avoid the spread of fire between buildings on adjoining allotments is verified when it is calculated that—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_84f8d22e-ab53-4373-b516-287123aad2d9">a building will not cause heat flux in excess of those set out in column 2 of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/134_0.4.0.xml#_744102a7-c0b0-4311-b642-07ec714742a4" id="_cd9ddd36-ebc8-41ca-a6a9-0d740067f67d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table H3V3</xref> at locations within the boundaries of an adjoining property set out in column 1 of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/134_0.4.0.xml#_744102a7-c0b0-4311-b642-07ec714742a4" id="_3c1b6dd1-7be5-4aa5-ba79-c739d04f17a2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table H3V3</xref> where another building may be constructed; and</li><li id="_f6cc10d8-60f5-4fe6-bfd4-84d23a17c1ea">when located at the distances from the allotment boundary set out in column 1 of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/134_0.4.0.xml#_744102a7-c0b0-4311-b642-07ec714742a4" id="_ad3afd05-2156-4e42-afa9-88146b254d02" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table H3V3</xref>, a building is capable of withstanding the heat flux set out in column 2 of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/134_0.4.0.xml#_744102a7-c0b0-4311-b642-07ec714742a4" id="_b82bec7b-d55f-4695-a49f-7d890e41bb25" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table H3V3</xref> without ignition.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_f9e3bcd5-c07e-493f-831a-11151ca6cd7f"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>H3V3 is equivalent to <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1784#_1e201098-155a-4311-8c35-a31d747b95ac" id="_4f82f700-52d8-41c2-9501-4f90f396176a" publishing-id="vol1" scope="external" type="clause">C1V1</xref> in NCC Volume One. Guidance on the use of <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1784#_1e201098-155a-4311-8c35-a31d747b95ac" id="_1191118c-8142-4807-8fed-3ca074f6c2f8" publishing-id="vol1" scope="external" type="clause">C1V1</xref> can be found in the Guide to NCC Volume One, and is applicable to the use of H3V3.</p></callout><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/134_0.4.0.xml" graph="None" id="_744102a7-c0b0-4311-b642-07ec714742a4"><num/><title id="_186eafd1-412c-4be5-9584-1c3080056e60"/></table-reference></clause>